        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12680.xml">letter to R. P. Hardy, 6 August [1880]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Hardy’s letter has not been found; see, however, the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12680.xml">letter to R. P. Hardy, 6 August [1880]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD was in Cambridge visiting <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1266.xml">Horace</ref> and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1267.xml">Ida Darwin</ref> from 14 to 19 August, and then in London with his brother, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1211.xml">Erasmus</ref>, until 21 August (CD’s ‘Journal’ (Appendix II)). </note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">No accounts for the Down Friendly Club have been found in the Darwin Archive–CUL or at Down House.</note>
            
